{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17584029","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17584029"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T07:36:05+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T07:36:05+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14277"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14277","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14277"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.32,0.31,0.14,0.13,0.1]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6972"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115528"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"6972","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6972"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14277"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97531"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"13"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"2091"},{"type":"tags","id":"3734"},{"type":"tags","id":"3879"},{"type":"tags","id":"5090"},{"type":"tags","id":"9485"},{"type":"tags","id":"11941"},{"type":"tags","id":"12795"},{"type":"tags","id":"12919"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"16370"},{"type":"contributions","id":"40125"},{"type":"contributions","id":"40437"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115528","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/115528"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 25-year-old man presents to the haematology clinic with a two-week history of a rapidly growing jaw mass. On examination, a large, firm mass is palpable on the left side of his jaw. Biopsy reveals a \u0027starry sky\u0027 appearance with numerous mitotic figures.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following chromosomal translocations is most likely to be found?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["t(8;14)","t(9;22)","t(15;17)","t(11;14)","t(14;18)"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe presentation is consistent with Burkitt lymphoma, a highly aggressive B-cell non-Hodgkin lymphoma. The rapidly growing jaw mass and \u0027starry sky\u0027 histological appearance are characteristic of this condition. The most common chromosomal translocation in Burkitt lymphoma is \u003Cstrong\u003Et(8;14)\u003C/strong\u003E, which results in overexpression of the c-MYC oncogene.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe t(8;14) translocation juxtaposes the c-MYC gene on chromosome eight with the immunoglobulin heavy chain locus on chromosome 14. This leads to consequent constitutive activation of c-MYC, a transcription factor that regulates multiple genes in cell proliferation, growth, and apoptosis. In Burkitt lymphoma, c-MYC overexpression leads to uncontrolled cell division and inhibition of programmed cell death, resulting in rapid tumour cell growth.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Et(9;22)\u003C/strong\u003E translocation, also known as the Philadelphia chromosome, is characteristic of chronic myeloid leukaemia and some cases of B-acute lymphoblastic leukaemia. It results in the BCR::ABL fusion protein, which leads to constitutive activation of tyrosine kinase activity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Et(15;17)\u003C/strong\u003E translocation is seen in acute promyelocytic leukaemia. This translocation results in the fusion of the PML and RARA genes, leading to arrested differentiation of myeloid precursors at the promyelocyte stage.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Et(11;14)\u003C/strong\u003E translocation is commonly seen in mantle cell lymphoma. It results in overexpression of cyclin D1, leading to dysregulation of the cell cycle.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Et(14;18)\u003C/strong\u003E translocation is characteristic of follicular lymphoma. It leads to overexpression of the BCL2 protein, which inhibits apoptosis.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Burkitt lymphoma is characterised by the t(8;14) translocation, which leads to overexpression of the c-MYC oncogene.","The c-MYC oncogene promotes rapid cell proliferation and inhibits apoptosis in Burkitt lymphoma cells.","Epstein-Barr virus (EBV) infection is associated with endemic Burkitt lymphoma and plays a role in B-cell transformation."],"references":["L\u00f3pez C, Burkhardt B, Chan JKC, Leoncini L, Mbulaiteye SM, Ogwang MD, et al. Burkitt lymphoma. Nat Rev Dis Primers. 2022 Dec 15;8(1):1\u201326.","Roschewski M, Staudt LM, Wilson WH. Burkitt\u2019s Lymphoma. New England Journal of Medicine. 2022 Sep 21;387(12):1111\u201322.","Kumar V, Abbas AK, Aster JC. Robbins and Cotran Pathologic Basis of Disease. 10th ed. Philadelphia: Elsevier; 2020; Chapter 17, pages 601-602."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97531"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14277"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97531","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/97531"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-24T11:29:39+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-24T11:29:39+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6972"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115528"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"13","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/13"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\ude78","name":"Haematology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:44+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"